---
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---
<LegalLayout title="Privacy Notice | NozzleNote by BMR" description="Privacy notice for NozzleNote by BMR, including current consent-gated GA4 website analytics, planned local-first app data direction, and future interest-list planning." eyebrow="Privacy notice" heading="Privacy Notice — current website analytics and planned app privacy direction." intro="This notice explains the current website analytics setup and the planned local-first privacy direction for the future NozzleNote desktop app. App, account, payment, license, cloud, mobile and support features are not public yet and will require review before launch." currentPath="/privacy/">
  <LegalSection title="Privacy contact"><p>Privacy contact: <a href="mailto:contact@nozzlenote.com">contact@nozzlenote.com</a></p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Current website data collection"><p>This static website does not provide accounts, checkout, support forms, newsletter forms, app downloads, license activation, cloud sync, or mobile app features. It does not intentionally collect names, emails, printer records, maintenance records, payment data, license data, or support messages through site forms.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Current website analytics and cookies"><p>When PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID is configured with a valid GA4 Measurement ID, the website offers basic Google Analytics 4 measurement only after a visitor accepts analytics cookies. The default state is analytics disabled. Visitors can accept or reject analytics cookies, and rejecting analytics does not block site access.</p><p>If accepted, GA4 may use cookies or identifiers to measure page views, traffic sources, referrers, scroll behavior, outbound clicks, and general engagement. If the measurement ID is missing or invalid, the website does not render the GA4 configuration and does not attempt to load GA4.</p><p>Visitors can use the footer “Cookie settings” control to reopen the choice UI later. If analytics consent is rejected after previously being accepted, the site stops future GA4 loads where practical and attempts to clear existing GA cookies.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Analytics limits"><ul><li>No advertising, remarketing, Google Signals, User-ID tracking, Google Ads linking, custom dimensions, e-commerce tracking, manual link-click instrumentation, form instrumentation, or manual personal-data collection has been added.</li><li>No form input is sent to GA4.</li><li>Website browsing is not described with broad privacy-by-default language. Local-first language is reserved for planned app maintenance records and local-first app data.</li></ul></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Future interest-list planning"><p>No active interest form is collecting data yet. A future interest form may collect an email address, user type, number of printers, printer models, and optional country/region or use case so visitors can request launch updates and share broad setup context.</p><p>The actual form provider, data categories, consent language, retention approach, and unsubscribe process must be disclosed before collection starts. Visitors should not submit printer serial numbers, private account details, payment data, sensitive personal information, or confidential maintenance records.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Future local-first app data direction"><p>NozzleNote by BMR is being developed with app maintenance records planned to stay local by default. Public app behavior, backups, exports, account features, license activation, cloud sync, mobile app functionality, and support workflows are not final and should be documented and reviewed before release.</p></LegalSection>
  <LegalSection title="Future or conditional data categories"><p>Future app, account, license, payment, support, cloud, mobile, catalog, or campaign features may require additional data categories and reviewed privacy language before launch. Privacy contact: <a href="mailto:contact@nozzlenote.com">contact@nozzlenote.com</a></p></LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
